- [Y] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.

---------------------------

## Issue

Attempting to call selfdestruct on a Ganache/testrpc deployed contract results in Base fee exceeds gas limit.

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Run Ganache(UI or cli) or testrpc
2. Migrate a simple contract using truffle or remix to Ganache (it is not necessary to use meta mask)
3. Using Remix to connect to the ganache node call the function that executes self destruct.

## Expected Behavior

The selfdestruct will succeed and any funds in the contract will be returned to the owner

## Actual Results

An Error occurs: Base Fee Exceeds Gas Limit

## Environment

* Operating System: Mac OS 10.13.4
* Ethereum client: Remix
* Truffle version (`truffle version`): Ganache CLI v6.1.0 (ganache-core: 2.1.0) with Solidity v0.4.23 (solc-js)
* node version (`node --version`): v8.9.4
* npm version (`npm --version`): 5.6.0

Test.sol
```
pragma solidity 0.4.23;
contract Test {
    address public owner;
    constructor() public {
        owner = msg.sender;
    }
    function destroy() onlyOwner public {
        selfdestruct(owner);
    }
    modifier onlyOwner() {
        require(msg.sender == owner);
        _;
    }
}
```

@phillipgibb This might be Remix related. I've run your code within Truffle using `truffle test` and been unable to reproduce. Can you see if the test below suceeds for you?

**Test**
```javascript 
const Test = artifacts.require('Test');

contract('Test', function(accounts){
  it('should selfdestruct', async function(){
    const instance = await Test.new();
    try {
      await instance.destroy();
      console.log('Success')
    } catch(err){
      console.log('Failure: ' + err);
    }
  });
})
```

